	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Honestly I don't think those particular SoC clone systems are interesting, nor do I think overclocking/LED mods are. To me overclocking seems like a silly macho fad thing that people should be over by now.</div><br />I don't overclock systems for 'macho fad appeal', it's a technical interest and a challenge. Maybe you're thinking of PC overclocking for ePenis 3Dmark points.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> I think FDS belt fixing/retuning type stuff would actually be more useful to people who can't read Japanese sites. Here are some projects I would be interested in seeing these projects (if I probably couldn't do them myself):</div><br />I don't own an FDS, or at least not a WHOLE FDS, just the RAM adapter. I would like to make a video about hooking that up to a PC to run FDS software however.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">-Upgrade FC/NES memory to 8K for dev purposes (just connect most significant A lines)<br />-Create a hardware debugger/stepper for NES using a save-state mechanism (OK so this one isn't so easy, especially not with discrete logic <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />-Create open HID compliant USB game pad with a microcontroller for people to use with newer more accurate emulators<br />-RGB -&gt; component transcoder using opamps for MD/PCE/SFC/NG etc<br />-Create a 74 series digital counter and RGB LED based JP/EN &amp; 50/60Hz import mod for MD/SAT using reset or something so they don't have to add ugly toggle switches. Maybe the same for SFC w/ 50/60Hz and CIC.</div><br />This all has EXTREMELY limited appeal. I doubt there will be many people who would honestly give a damn in most cases.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">-USB adapted Dreamcast coders cable</div><br />Did you somehow miss the 'classic'/'vintage' bit about my post?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">-Multi-console power supply</div><br />This is just boring...  these suggestions are really coming out of left field. Did you read my post? These are not even remotely related topics for a video honestly.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Also If I had to do a overclocking mod, I would do a VCO in a PLL with the original oscillator so it's reliable and so people could tune instead of switching between different crystals which seems inelegant.</div>
<br />Actually, my current implementation uses a variable oscillator card with 3 crystals and an adjustable multiplier. Rather nice for on-the-fly clock adjustment. However I am currently working on rigging up a proper square wave generator with adjustable frequency to the FC2 and MD1 with a BNC cable and termination for the maximum possible stability. For the MD and FC, using a multiple of the bus clock isn't necessary to achieve very high speeds-- and any stability issues are not caused by lack of sync with the bus, but from timing issues. In either case these are extremely uncommon to cause real showstopping problems.

		

		</td>
